     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Results achieved</narrative>
     <narrative xml:lang="FR">R&#xE9;sultats atteints</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="FR">Parmi les r&#xE9;sultats obtenus jusqu&#x2019;en mars 2012 : Ce projet a eu une grande incidence sur le cadre de r&#xE9;glementation des affaires en Ukraine. En effet, il a d&#xE9;bouch&#xE9; sur la promulgation de 68 lois progressistes, dont des lois importantes qui simplifient la d&#xE9;livrance de licences ou de permis d&#x2019;exploitation de commerces, et sur l&#x2019;am&#xE9;lioration ou l&#x2019;&#xE9;limination de plus de 2 177 proc&#xE9;dures administratives, mesure qui permettra au secteur priv&#xE9; de r&#xE9;aliser chaque ann&#xE9;e d&#x2019;importantes &#xE9;conomies, gr&#xE2;ce &#xE0; la diminution consid&#xE9;rable des exigences &#xE0; respecter. R&#xE9;cemment, le projet a appuy&#xE9; la modification de la loi relative aux permis; ainsi, le pays a pu ramener &#xE0; 135 la longue liste des 200 permis requis aux termes de diverses lois ukrainiennes.</narrative>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Results as of March 2012 include: The project has had a major impact on the business regulatory environment in Ukraine, resulting in the enactment of 68 progressive legal acts, including key laws that streamline business licensing and permits, and in the improvement or elimination of more than 2,177 administrative procedures, which will save the private sector a considerable amount of money annually, by significantly reducing the number of requirements for businesses. Most recently, the project supported changes to the Law on Permits, which further reduced the exhaustive list of required permits across various legal acts in Ukraine from more than 200 to a simplified 135.</narrative>
    </description>
   </indicator>
